<subSubSection pageId="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[707,1194,699,1464]" pageId="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,836,805,826]" pageId="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguishable from superficially similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[910,1002,831,852]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis box="[910,1002,831,852]" italics="true" pageId="13">P. amplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the yellow line on the sides of the elytra and yellow mark near the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[707,1194,699,1464]" pageId="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,914,911,932]" pageId="13">Description. Size</emphasis>
: Length 5.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[707,783,938,959]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="13" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[793,849,938,959]" pageId="13">Form</emphasis>
: As in 
<figureCitation box="[920,1004,938,959]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="23.[197,237,1478,1497]" captionTargetBox="[174,1193,193,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-81@23.[172,1193,192,1454]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figs. 104–109. Pujoliclerus species, habitus. 104) P. orellana; 105) P. oxinus; 106) P. alajuela; 107) P. megacavus;" pageId="13">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1013,1130,938,959]" pageId="13">Integument</emphasis>
: Head mostly yellow, with rectangular black marking on vertex; antenna mostly black, antennomere 9 partially yellow, 10 yellow; pronotal disc broadly black, sides yellow; elytra mostly yellow, with yellow line at sides and with yellow macula near apex; legs mostly yellow, tibiae infuscated; pterothorax and abdomen brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[986,1040,1124,1145]" pageId="13">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes narrower than frons (12:15); funicular antennomeres considerably expanded (
<figureCitation box="[912,987,1177,1198]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[175,216,1487,1506]" captionTargetBox="[167,1170,207,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[151,1172,183,1487]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 21–38. Pujoliclerus species, antennae. 21) P. helvinus; 22) P. maracayensis; 23) P. bilineatus; 24) P. calceatus; 25) P. corumba; 26) P. ovatus; 27) P. wappesi; 28) P. amplus; 29) P. flavoapicalus; 30) P. gilvus; 31) P. hermani; 32) P. alajuela; 33) P. orellana; 34) P. megacavus; 35) P. oxinus; 36) P. alboordinus; 37) P. apolegmus; 38) P. catarina." pageId="13">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1082,1177,1198]" pageId="13">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum quadrate (35:35), lateral tubercle very prominent (
<figureCitation box="[714,791,1230,1251]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[175,215,1395,1414]" captionTargetBox="[151,1155,183,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-114@18.[151,1172,183,1383]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs. 48–61. Pujoliclerus species, pronota. 48) P. helvinus; 49) P. maracayensis; 50) P. modestus; 51) P. bilineatus; 52) P. calceatus; 53) P. corumba; 54) P. flavolimbatus; 55) P. ovatus; 56) P. wappesi; 57) P. amplus; 58) P. flavoapicalus; 59) P. gilvus; 60) P. hermani; 61) P. orellana." pageId="13">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
); epipleural fold gradually diminishing to elytral apex; asetiferous punctures prominent to elytral half. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[852,952,1283,1304]" pageId="13">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Abdomen not available
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[707,1194,699,1464]" pageId="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,899,1310,1331]" pageId="13">Natural History.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[955,994,1310,1331]" pageId="13">type</typeStatus>
